{
  "texts": [
    "Deep Learning, a significant breakthrough in ML, has rapidly gained traction across various application domains such as computer vision, speech recognition, and natural language processing, among many others.",
    "Unlike traditional human-crafted ML systems, a DL model automatically learns features and decision-making processes through its multi-level representation.",
    "The purpose of this section is to provide the reader with an overview of DL, laying the foundation for a better understanding of the subsequent content in this paper.",
    "Consequently, the next section presents an outline of the key DL models utilized in the generation, detection, and prevention of deepfakes.",
    "In the following, some of the most common DL architectures used within deepfakes topic are presented."
  ]
}